    <h1 class="center">Overview</h1>
    <input type="checkbox" class="read-more-state" id="overview-post" />
    <ul class="read-more-wrap liststyle">
        <li><p class="about">Underrepresented artist refers to a person who performs creative activities, and attempts to generate income by selling art pieces, but is not being represented or does not own a gallery.</p></li>
        <li><p class="about">The field of art is one of the many industries where there is a lack of diversity.  The <a href="https://www.arts.gov/" target="_blank">National Endowment for the Arts (NEA)</a> have released various reports on the demographics of the artists.  It was found out that women are not strongly represented in this field and that there are more white than non-white artists.  The NEA also released a research report showing that in the United States there are a total of 2.5 million artists which represent 1.8% of the total labor; 84% or 2.1 million were employed in primary jobs as artists, 12.5% or 0.315 million were employed in secondary jobs as artists, and 3.5% or 0.088 million were unemployed.</p></li>
        <li class="read-more-target"><p class="about">Moreover, there is a perception by the society that making art is frivolous or only recreational.  The societal contributions of artists are not well understood despite of its socioeconomic contributions.  However, in 2013, arts and cultural production contributed $704.2 billion to the U.S. economy, a 32.5 percent increase since 1998 <a href="https://www.arts.gov/sites/default/files/ACPSA_fact_sheet_feb2016.pdf" target="_blank">[1]</a>.   Also, artists represent a larger group than the legal profession (lawyers, judges, and paralegals), medical doctors (physicians, surgeons, and dentists), or agricultural workers (farmers, ranchers, foresters, and fishers) <a href="https://www.arts.gov/sites/default/files/ArtistsInWorkforce_ExecSum.pdf" target="_blank">[2]</a>.</p></li>
        <li class="read-more-target"><p class="about">Internationally, there is a significant number of underrepresented artists, but the percentages in terms of gender and race may vary.  It is imperative to provide a support structure for the artists in the US and across the world.</p></li>
        <li class="read-more-target"><p class="about">Imagine how the labor force will be strengthened should the artists be encouraged and enabled in their creative pursuits.  By consuming and experiencing art differently, these individuals are empowered and there will be impactful contributions on the socioeconomic growths of every country.</p></li>
    </ul>
