    <ul class="read-more-wrap liststyle">
        <li><p class="about">Showcased is a non-profit organization that aims to generate additional revenue streams for underrepresented visual artists, photographers, designers, and other artists by exhibiting and selling unique arts online. Another objective of the organization is to establish the online presence and branding of the underrepresented artists by leveraging on Search Engine Optimization (SEO) and developing a mobile application using Augmented Reality technology.</p></li>
        <li class="read-more-target"><p class="about">Without being able to showcase the artworks in onsite galleries, there is a limited market for arts, which makes the internet a significant channel to reach out to art collectors, enthusiasts, and people who are interested in purchasing art pieces.  Nevertheless, despite the various social media platforms such as Instagram, Facebook, and Pinterest, selling art online is challenging because there is no software built to address the concerns specific for this niche.  Showcased uses business analytics to understand what the buyersâ€™ preferences are.  This tool is also used when an artist is being submitted and presented to the gallery, museum, and store partners.  In addition to, Showcased has partnered with Amazon FBA to handle the logistics in delivering the item to the customer.  With its end to end solution, from Marketing to Logistics, the artist would be able to focus on its creative activities instead of worrying on how he could pay the bills while still pursuing his passions.</p></li>
